{"word":"εἴποτε","slug":"εἴποτε","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n31163\" key=\"ei)/pote\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">εἴποτε</orth> or <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">εἴ ποτε</orth>, <sense id=\"n31163.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">if ever</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:39\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.39</biblScope> </bibl>; strengthd. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">εἴ ποτε δή</foreign> ib.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:503\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">503</biblScope> </bibl>: used in asking a favour of any one, to call something to his mind, for <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">εἴποτ᾽ ἔην γε</foreign>, i.e. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">as surely as</tr_> he was. </sense> <sense n=\"II\" id=\"n31163.1\" level=\"2\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> indirect, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">if</tr_> or <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">whether ever</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:2:97\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.97</biblScope></bibl>, etc.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}